EXperiment-5
============
Create a Node JS application for user login system.

Aim:
----
The aim of the experiment is to know how to perform user registration and login process using nodejs and mongodb

Building a user login system in Node.js involves several key components, including server setup with Express.js, database integration, password hashing with bcrypt, and session/token management using JSON Web Tokens (JWT) or sessions. 

In short will use the following technologies

NodeJS & Express â€“ Backend server and routing
MongoDB â€“ NoSQL database for user data
Mongoose â€“ Object Data Modeling (ODM) library for MongoDB and NodeJS.
EJS â€“ Templating engine for views
Passport.js - Authentication middleware for NodeJS applications.


Core Technologies
-----------------
A typical Node.js login system uses the following technologies:

Node.js & Express: The runtime environment and the web framework for building the server and handling routes.

Database: A database (e.g., MongoDB) to store user credentials.

Bcrypt: A library for securely hashing and comparing passwords.

Authentication Middleware: Tools like Passport.js for simple, modular authentication, or JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for stateless, token-based authentication.

Templating Engine: An engine like EJS, Handlebars (hbs), or Pug to render the front-end login and registration forms.

Project setup:
--------------
mkdir node-login-system
cd node-login-system
npm init -y
npm install express mongoose bcryptjs jsonwebtoken dotenv

